HEADWORD: bourtree
<hw>bourtree</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>common black-fruited shrub or small
tree (<spn>Sambucus nigra</spn>) of Europe and Asia; -- the fruit is
used for wines and jellies.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> black elder, common elder, elderberry, European
elder.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

